Going through some stuff today and came across this box.  Ron from  
paranormalsystems.com only sold a dozen of these and i think 11 came back to  him.  
That project was a disaster from start to finish.  I tried to  help, but 
cheap parts were used to build it.

I took it apart today to look and see what i can do to improve it.   The 
first thing i noticed was a crappy antenna, so i swapped it out with one  from 
a broken radio sitting here.

Reception did improve, but it still sucks.  It&#39;s like polishing a  
turd......Sorry, i know that was disgusting.

This box is AM Random mode only.  I think when you try to get too  advanced 
with building these, that&#39;s when the problems start.  Simple is  the best 
way to do it.  I&#39;ve attached the raw audio of the test with it and  some 
sample files i got.

Now i guess it goes back into the closet where i got it from.

-Steve




